sentences: Julia Sigova (born 1982) is a Belarusian-Swedish classical concert pianist.
In 2008 she was awarded a scholarship as the Best Female pianist in the Öresund Region and in 2011 she was chosen as the Best Female Artist in Sweden by Fredrika Bremer Association.
In 2008 she was awarded a scholarship as the Best Female pianist in the Öresund Region and in 2011 she was chosen as the Best Female Artist in Sweden by Fredrika Bremer Association.
Since Julia's debut with The Malmö Symphony Orchestra in 2010, she performed at "La Biennale" in Venice, Båstad Chamber Music Festival and St Martin-in-the-Fields among others.
